    <item>
      <title>尽管发表敌意言论，特朗普仍寻求与中国领导人建立更深层次的联系</title>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/us/politics/trump-speech-china-xi.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[中国官员似乎认为，特朗普总统指责中国干预 2020 年美国大选是出于国内政治而非外交政策。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/us/politics/trump-speech-china-xi.html</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 21:29:41 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普的选举主张和“储蓄法案”推动共和党反应冷淡立法者</title>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/us/politics/trump-election-save-act-republicans-midterms.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[大多数共和党人议员们对总统关于选举脆弱性的说法几乎没有说什么，他似乎也没有对他所支持的投票限制法案采取行动。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/us/politics/trump-election-save-act-republicans-midterms.html</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 20:53:40 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>股市因对科技和人工智能的焦虑而下跌开支</title>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/business/stocks-ai-tech-wall-street.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[在全球人工智能主导地位的竞赛中，来自中国的竞争日益激烈，投资者对此越来越感到不安。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/business/stocks-ai-tech-wall-street.html</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 20:17:16 GMT</pubDate>
